# Google Calendar Backend Integration Plan

This plan outlines the steps to integrate the official Google Calendar API into the StopBully360 backend, replacing the front-end template URL with a robust backend solution.

## User Action Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> To implement a backend integration with Google Calendar, you **must** have a Google Cloud Project with the Google Calendar API enabled.
> 1. Go to the [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/).
> 2. Enable the **Google Calendar API**.
> 3. Create a **Service Account** (for a centralized school calendar) OR **OAuth 2.0 Client credentials** (if you want counselors to log in with their own Google accounts).
> 4. For this plan, we will assume a **Service Account** approach where the backend uses a generic school calendar account to create and send invites. You will need to provide a [serviceAccountKey.json](file:///c:/Users/User/Downloads/stopbully360/stopbully360/backend/serviceAccountKey.json) or similar credentials file to the backend.

